The paper deals with geometric objects and their properties, such as convex objects, halfspaces, and rectangles, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The concept of centerpoints and strong centerpoints is related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), which are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and approximation, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively.
